race.description: Pj Murphy Real Estate Maiden Plate
race.comment: KING KAUFFO (5) is a three-year-old with just a few starts and is heading the right way. Second-up from a break ran on hard over this trip to place and will strip even fitter. Drops nicely in the weights with the claim for Kennedy and looks hard to hold out. CORAL JET (2) has raced twice and although yet to place hasn't been far from the winner at each. Looks suited by the extra ground and has upside. BANNERLU (6) is a lightly raced mare who put the writing on the wall last time when trying to lead throughout over 1400m at Wangaratta. Has upside and should take catching. MIDNIGHT IN MINORI (7) is one of the more experienced in the race and is overdue for a win. Has placed last two, the latest coming off a wide gate. Having first try this longer trip and draws much better. Among the leading hopes. ALL THE MOVES (1) resumed from a long break in the same race as MIDNIGHT IN MINORI and finished fourth. Fitter and can improve sharply.
